phi m, n plus 1.

00:54:38.320 --> 00:54:39.250
So what's the rule?

00:54:39.250 --> 00:54:40.480
It takes this state
to this state,

00:54:40.480 --> 00:54:42.605
this state to this state,
this state to this state.

00:54:42.605 --> 00:54:45.574
And since we can extend--
since these are a basis,

00:54:45.574 --> 00:54:47.990
then that tells us how this
acts on an arbitrary function,

00:54:47.990 --> 00:54:50.000
because it acts on the
superposition as acting

00:54:50.000 --> 00:54:51.610
on each term.

00:54:51.610 --> 00:54:54.310
So we can define it in this
