00:55:45.280 --> 00:55:50.220
If we write a dagger
a is equal to n,

00:55:50.220 --> 00:55:52.580
then the commutation relation
for this-- so the energy

00:55:52.580 --> 00:55:54.340
operator for the
harmonic oscillator

00:55:54.340 --> 00:55:58.290
was equal to h bar
omega n plus 1/2.

00:55:58.290 --> 00:56:01.610
That's what we
derived last time.

00:56:01.610 --> 00:56:05.000
If we define a dagger a
as n, then the commutator

00:56:05.000 --> 00:56:08.280
of n with a dagger is a dagger.

00:56:08.280 --> 00:56:11.970
And the commutator of n
with a is equal to minus a.

00:56:15.590 --> 00:56:26.240
