01:16:31.060 --> 01:16:33.750
So this tells us
something very lovely.

01:16:33.750 --> 01:16:36.400
This tells us that if we're in
a state with a definite value

01:16:36.400 --> 01:16:41.970
of x, what must be true of our
uncertainty in the value of p?

01:16:41.970 --> 01:16:45.887
It can't be 0, because if our
uncertainty in the knowledge p

01:16:45.887 --> 01:16:47.970
were 0, that would mean
we were in a p eigenstate.

01:16:47.970 --> 01:16:49.980
We would have
definite value of p.

01:16:49.980 --> 01:16:53.639
So if a delta x is 0, delta
